  "number": 2885,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2885",
  "title": " fix(ie): do not rely on Object.assign ",
  "body": "We have had reports of users wanting to use InstantSearch.js with IE and that was failing because there are some parts of the code base that rely on Object.assign. We were also using _.assign as a polyfill in other parts.\r\n\r\nSince both have the same semantic as {...a} and we use the latest already often in the code, let's move to that (and it's correctly [polyfilled by Babel](https://babeljs.io/repl/#?babili=false&browsers=&build=&builtIns=false&code_lz=IYAgvCDewFwgLATgL4CgBG4rrgIgCYBm-AzrmgMZaQB0dwANCHTeskA&debug=false&forceAllTransforms=false&shippedProposals=false&circleciRepo=&evaluate=false&fileSize=false&lineWrap=false&presets=es2015%2Ces2016%2Ces2017%2Creact%2Cstage-0%2Cstage-1%2Cstage-2%2Cstage-3%2Ces2015-loose&prettier=false&targets=&version=6.26.0&envVersion=))",
